title: Grateful Dead Live at Radio City Music Hall on 1980-10-30
lineage: 10Ó 1/4 track Reels (Revox A-77 playback) -> Lexicon Lambda (24/96) -> Logic (mastering: speed correction, track indexing, dithering to 16/44.1) -> AIFF -> Xact (sbe correction) -> wav -> flac; Transfer (November 2009) and mastering (October 2017) by Alan Bershaw
description:
Set 1

Deep Elem Blues, Dark Hollow, I've Been All Around This World, On The Road Again, To Lay Me Down, Heaven Help The Fool, Ripple

Set 2

Alabama Getaway > Promised Land, Peggy-O, Mama Tried > Mexicali Blues, Loser, Minglewood Blues, Althea > Lost Sailor > Saint Of Circumstance

Set 3

Shakedown Street, Samson And Delilah, He's Gone > Truckin' > Drums* > The Other One* > Wharf Rat > Good Lovin'

E: Johnny B. Goode

Set 1 Acoustic

* - w/ Billy Cobham

reviews.review_text: HIPPY HALLOWEEN  2017  !!! ( ^.^ ) Very Nice Indeed. Thanks Alan. This Is The One We've Been Waiting For. Crisp As An Autumn Apple And Just As Sweet 'n' Crunchy. For Always And Forever Grateful.

37 years and one day ago This is the stuff - the stuff of legends.  Oh how I wish I had been at these acoustic shows.  A favorite side of the Dead for me.

This recording is excellent.  The music is free and flowing.  The best of both worlds coming together for a magic performance/recording.

Thank you for posting this

So good Great transfer and legendary gig. 

Loved hearing some of these tunes on the Dead Ahead video release way back. This was a spirited time from the band and clearly by 10/30 they had plenty of comfort in this acoustic/electric format, notwithstanding the rowdy crowd. 

Acoustic set standouts? All of them! That "Deep Elum" swings, that "On The Road Again," is quintessential, imho more pleasing than Pigpen's early era rendering. "To Lay Me Down," is sublime, indeed in it's finest form. "Heaven Help The Fool," instrumental reveals the subtle brilliance behind this tune, that was harder to spot in the studio rendering. 

The electric sets are strong. Bill Cobham guesting first and only time on drums-> other 1.. 

Thanks for this.
Just love it!! OK, my kind of GD.Love the era,recording is fantastic as well.A Big thank you for. This upload.
